hb_stats1d

Reads x-y pairs and computes mean and standard deviation
of y for the x binned according to min/max/increment 
specified with the -R argument. Input and output files can be
specified -- or the stdin and stdout devices will be used

Usage:  hb_stats1d input_file_list [-O<output_file>]  -R<min/max/incr> 
 [-O] : specifies optional output file
        default is stdout 
  -R  : specify minimum/maximum/[delta] to create x bins. 
        ex: -R1920/1995/5    default delta is 1 

